<a name="sF9086D6D02065DF39E78881962093EA0"></a><div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:right;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Exhibit 99.1</font></div></div><br><div style="line-height:174%;text-align:center;"><img src="gntximage2015a04.jpg" style="height:80px;width:240px;"></div><div style="line-height:174%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:center;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">GENTEX REPORTS SECOND QUARTER 2015 FINANCIAL RESULTS</font></div><div style="line-height:232%;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">ZEELAND, MI </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">--</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;(Marketwired - July 23</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">,</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;2015) - Gentex Corporation (NASDAQ:&#160;GNTX) the Zeeland, Michigan-based manufacturer of automotive automatic-dimming rearview mirrors, automotive electronics, dimmable aircraft windows, and fire protection products, today reported financial results for the </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">three months ended June 30, 2015</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">.</font></div><div style="line-height:232%;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">For the </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">second quarter</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;of 2015, the Company is pleased to report net sales of </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">$379.3 million</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">, which was an increase of </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">12%</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;compared to net sales of </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">$338.4 million</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;in the </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">second quarter</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;of 2014.  The Company's continued growth in sales has been accomplished despite worldwide light vehicle production  that declined </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">1%</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;in the second quarter of 2015 in the Company's primary markets versus the second quarter of 2014, in addition to foreign currency fluctuations that accounted for approximately 1% of revenue headwind during the second quarter of 2015. </font></div><div style="line-height:232%;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">The gross profit margin in the </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">second quarter</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;of 2015 was </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">38.4%</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">, compared with a gross profit margin of </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">39.7%</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;in the </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">second quarter</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;of 2014.  The primary drivers affecting gross profit margin on a year over year basis were annual customer price reductions, unfavorable product mix and currency rate fluctuations, which were partially offset by purchasing cost reductions. </font></div><div style="line-height:232%;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">Operating income for the second quarter of 2015 increased </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">8%</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;to </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">$108.1 million</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">, when compared to operating income of </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">$99.8 million</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;for the second quarter of 2014.  Adjusted Operating Income for the second quarter of 2015 increased 12% compared to the second quarter of 2014. </font></div><div style="line-height:232%;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">Other Income in the second quarter of 2015 decreased </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">60%</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;to </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">$2.3 million</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;compared with other income of $5.8 million in the second quarter of 2014, primarily due to lower realized gains on the sale of equity investments.  In the second quarter of 2014, the gains in the quarter were higher than normalized levels given the strength in equity markets and the Company's re-balancing of its investment portfolio following the HomeLink acquisition in 2013.</font></div><br><div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><a name="sF9086D6D02065DF39E78881962093EA0"></a><div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:right;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Exhibit 99.1</font></div></div><br><div style="line-height:232%;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">Net income for the </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">second quarter</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;of 2015 decreased 3% to </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">$74.6 million</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;compared with net income of </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">$76.7 million</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;in the </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">second quarter</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;of 2014.  Adjusted Net Income increased by 12% for the second quarter of 2015 when compared to Adjusted Net Income for the second quarter of 2014.</font></div><div style="line-height:232%;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">Earnings per diluted share in the </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">second quarter</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;of 2015 were </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">$0.25</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">, compared with earnings per diluted share of </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">$0.26</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;in the </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">second quarter</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;of 2014, which reflects the December 31, 2014 stock split, effected in the form of a 100% stock dividend.   The reported earnings per diluted share for the second quarter of 2015 decreased 4% on a quarter over quarter basis, however Adjusted Earnings per Diluted Share for the second quarter of 2015 were up 11% compared to Adjusted Earnings per Diluted Share for the second quarter 2014.</font></div><div style="line-height:232%;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">Automotive net sales in the </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">second quarter</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;of 2015 were $370.5 million, up 12% compared with automotive net sales of $329.6 million in the </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">second quarter</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;of 2014, primarily due to an </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">11%</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;increase in auto dimming mirror unit shipments.</font></div><div style="line-height:232%;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">Other net sales, which includes dimmable aircraft windows and fire protection products, were $8.8 million in the </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">second quarter</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;of 2015, compared with $8.9 million in the </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">second quarter</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;of 2014. </font></div><div style="line-height:232%;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:232%;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;color:#333333;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;">Other</font></div><div style="line-height:232%;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;color:#333333;">During the second quarter of 2015, the Company repurchased 1.4 million shares for approximately $25.1 million, and through six months ended June 30, 2015 the Company has repurchased 2.8 million shares for  $50.1 million.  The Company intends to continue to repurchase additional shares of its common stock in the future depending on macroeconomic issues, market trends and other factors that the Company deems appropriate.  As of June 30, 2015, the Company has approximately 3.4 million shares remaining available for repurchase under its most recently announced share repurchase plan.</font></div><div style="line-height:232%;text-align:left;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:232%;text-align:left;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;">Future Estimates</font></div><div style="line-height:232%;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">The Company&#8217;s forecasts for light vehicle production for the second half and calendar year 2015 are based on the IHS Automotive July 2015 forecast for light vehicle production in North America, Europe, Japan and Korea.  </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:center;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><br><div><div Like all non-GAAP financial measures, these non-GAAP measures are intended to supplement, not to replace, GAAP measures.
